1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,240
Your ears aren't working properly.
Can you hear me?

2
00:00:03,320 --> 00:00:05,600
-Can you hear me at all?
-I can hear you just fine!

3
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:07,120
PREVIOUSLY

4
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,280
Why did you kiss me?

5
00:00:08,360 --> 00:00:11,200
I'm kissing my friend,
the way people kiss their pets.

6
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,640
<i>I had a lot of fun flying a kite today.</i>

7
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:16,640
<i>Prince Mai sure takes good care of you.</i>

8
00:00:16,720 --> 00:00:18,120
I guess I am now useless.

9
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,920
<i>Would you be up for a bet?</i>

10
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,920
<i>-What are we betting, Your Highness?</i>
<i>-The professor, perhaps.</i>

11
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:26,200
CIVIL SERVANTS SCHOOL

12
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:27,120
Good morning.

13
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,520
My name is Dech,

14
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:31,000
and this is my friend, Chai.

15
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:33,560
Nice to meet you.

16
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,840
My name is Sak.

17
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:37,320
Nice to meet you too.

18
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:39,720
Well done, sirs.

19
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:42,840
In two months' time,
when our lessons are over,

20
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:46,360
I won't be able to tell you Siamese
apart from the French.

21
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:50,920
Are you leaving for France… in two months?

22
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:54,360
What are your plans
after these two months?

23
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:56,160
Plans?

24
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,640
Any plans to stay at the Legation in Siam?

25
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:02,400
I will continue working for the Legation,

26
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:05,600
but I don't get to decide
where I'll be sent.

27
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:09,200
You are, by blood,
a grandson of the Suriyakorn family.

28
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:13,000
I'm sure His Highness would be pleased
if you were to be stationed here in Siam.

29
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:17,320
You know that's not what I want, Thee.

30
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:20,760
I want to return to France

31
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:23,920
to spend time with my father
and take care of my sister.

32
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,480
I am not…

33
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,840
a part of your plans, then?

34
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,360
What about you?

35
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,520
Do you have plans to move
to France with me?

36
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,440
France…

37
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,640
It's not right, is it?

38
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,760
We each have our own homes.

39
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:56,240
Our own responsibilities.

40
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:58,720
We each have endless duties to attend to.

41
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:04,400
We chose to be together now

42
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:08,160
because we wanted to have
no regrets, didn't we?

43
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,680
I think that in these next two months,

44
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:13,520
it would be best
if we didn't bring this up again.

45
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:17,160
I don't want either of us
to shed any more tears.

46
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,320
I'm here to pick you up.

47
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,560
Allow me a moment
to finish reading my father's letter.

48
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,880
What does it say?

49
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:14,400
"This is a navaratna ring."

50
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:16,399
"It belonged to your Mother Rung."

51
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:19,800
"She wanted it to be
your 25th birthday present."

52
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:23,360
"Wear it for good luck."

53
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:29,440
"I would be more than happy if you were
to give it to someone you love, son."

54
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:32,480
Someone you love?

55
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:38,000
Who would be so lucky?

56
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,880
THE KING RECEIVED TWO PIECES
OF GOOD NEWS…

57
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:48,200
You translated it really well, Mr. Tiwa.

58
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,080
You did a better job at it than I would.

59
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,960
You praise me too much, Rati.

60
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:54,360
One is a superb teacher.

61
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:57,320
The other is an amazing student.

62
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,680
Before I return to France,

63
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:04,560
you will have mastered the language
and be able to work on official documents.

64
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:07,720
That would be very good indeed.

65
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,160
I want to work.

66
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:11,920
I want to help my father out
with his work.

67
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,360
And you will.

68
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:18,040
You'll leave in two months,
won't you, Mr. Rati?

69
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:20,360
I will miss you dearly.

70
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:24,000
I'll write often.

71
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,760
We still have two months.

72
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:28,280
No need to speak
as if he's leaving in two days.

73
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,560
That's a beautiful ring.

74
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:36,640
Who gave it to you?

75
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,200
My mother.

76
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,040
It's an early birthday gift.

77
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:46,560
And she said you should give it
to someone you love.

78
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,440
Who are you going to give it to, Mr. Rati?

79
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,520
It must be Thee.

80
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,960
If it were me, I'd give it to Thee.

81
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,800
Because you are the best.

82
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:07,520
I guess we'll let the professor decide
whether or not I am the best to him.

83
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,160
Are your hands feeling stiff?

84
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,560
Am I not the person you love?

85
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,880
I'm not answering that.

86
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:41,920
Rati.

87
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,160
You're teasing me.

88
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,880
Thee.

89
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,760
Yes?

90
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,320
Can you do me a favor?

91
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:10,960
These news articles were translated
by Professor Rati's students?

92
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:11,920
Yes.

93
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,760
I believe they need some more time
to master the language.

94
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,960
Thee, my child.

95
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,200
What brings you all the way to my office?

96
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,000
Someone is here to see you, Father.

97
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,640
Leave us for now.

98
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:49,120
I wanted to be the one to give you
this translation, my lord.

99
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,480
This is, by far, the best translation

100
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,320
out of all of your students,
Professor Rati.

101
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,320
Did you translate this?

102
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,400
It wasn't me.

103
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:11,600
It was translated by Mr. Tiwa.

104
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:16,200
Tiwa has always been interested
in languages.

105
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:19,800
Professor Rati was kind enough
to give him lessons at home.

106
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:23,160
I believe Tiwa is now more fluent
than he ever was before.

107
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,920
I am certain that once
I am no longer here,

108
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:32,600
Mr. Tiwa will be able to assist you
in this regard, my lord.

109
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,000
If you would like to see for yourself,

110
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,159
tomorrow at noon,

111
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:41,600
Ms. Ruedi and Mr. Tiwa are hosting
a party for my birthday.

112
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,560
I extend an invitation to you, sir.

113
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:55,920
Here it is.

114
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:57,520
Thank you.

115
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,480
-Here, sir.
-Good.

116
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:04,560
I'll leave the place to you for a bit.

117
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,240
Of course.

118
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,560
Mek. Mek!

119
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,640
Monsieur Mek.

120
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,160
Mek!

121
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:19,440
Ugh! Why are you yelling?

122
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,960
I can hear you just fine.

123
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:24,920
The Ministry of the Royal Household
is looking for ten French translators.

124
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:26,920
Really?

125
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,200
The exam is one month from now.

126
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,800
You need to apply, do you hear me?

127
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,520
There is no need to hesitate.

128
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,080
I will go with you.

129
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,560
But my hearing…

130
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:42,240
Your hearing will get better.

131
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:45,160
If it doesn't, you still have me.

132
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:47,560
I'll be there to help you.

133
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,160
How lucky I am to have you with me.

134
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,120
Thanks, Dech.

135
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:03,800
Anything you need my help with? We can
get it done quickly so we can study.

136
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:07,760
Here.

137
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,240
Clean this place.

138
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,680
Start over there.

139
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:12,800
Thanks, Dech.

140
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,720
Hey.

141
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,440
What are you standing there for? Go on.

142
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,400
This guy sure doesn't hold back.

143
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:26,000
What was that?

144
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,440
Isn't your hearing bad?

145
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,600
What are you staring at?

146
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:37,720
I'm just watching you work. Go on.

147
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:13,200
Here.

148
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,280
Open wide.

149
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,400
SRISAMAI PHOTOGRAPHY

150
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,680
What else do you want to do?

151
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:46,000
Waterfall. I want to go to a waterfall.

152
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,920
Waterfall…
You want to visit a waterfall?

153
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:50,640
Yes.

154
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:55,640
I believe we'll need to stay overnight
if we go to a waterfall.

155
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,480
Am I asking for too much?

156
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,000
Not at all.

157
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:07,000
I'd love to go anywhere with you.

158
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,280
I'll be sure to take you.

159
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,960
I'll take that as a promise, Thee.

160
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:16,520
Tell me all your wishes.

161
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,280
During your last two months in Siam,

162
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,920
I'll make you the happiest
you've ever been in your life.

163
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:28,240
I will make sure to savor
these happy moments.

164
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:31,880
Let's go.

165
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,600
You're making it yourself?

166
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:55,600
Of course.

167
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:58,040
It's your birthday.
I have to do something special.

168
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,280
I didn't know you cooked.

169
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,480
I asked Buaphan for the recipe.

170
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:04,760
I guarantee it will be
just as good as hers.

171
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,400
Bring coconut milk to a boil,
but make sure not to reduce it.

172
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:13,200
Add shallot, mackerel, and lotus stem.

173
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,800
Then simply season the soup.

174
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:18,000
That's simply the hard part, I think.

175
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:22,120
Why don't you go and stand over there?

176
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:24,400
Why?

177
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,800
I'm afraid

178
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:28,840
I'll over-sweeten the soup if you're here.

179
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,200
Make it overly sweet, then.

180
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,880
By all means.

181
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,200
…RECEIVED TWO PIECES OF GOOD NEWS…

182
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,280
It's done.

183
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:27,120
Rati has tried it, and approved.

184
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:29,680
I'm so relieved.

185
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:31,280
Thank you for lending me your kitchen.

186
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,960
Is something wrong?

187
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,520
This matter between you and Mr. Rati…

188
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:44,600
Are you certain about it?

189
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:50,040
Well… what do you think, Ms. Ruedi?

190
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:55,640
I am happy to see you happy, of course.

191
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,720
I can't help but worry for you though.

192
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:06,600
In the future, you and Mr. Rati will face
so many obstacles and difficulties.

193
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,720
Maybe even worse than
the ones I faced, sir.

194
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:18,400
To go against the grain of society
is indeed a struggle.

195
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,800
But when I consider it,

196
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:29,200
to go against my own heart

197
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:31,880
would be a far worse torment.

198
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:38,600
I will not spend the next
20 or 30 years of my life in fear.

199
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:43,720
I don't want to regret
not fighting for what I want.

200
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:51,040
I will do everything possible
to ensure that Rati and I can be together.

201
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:01,880
You are much braver
than I thought, Mr. Thee.

202
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:05,320
I thank you for your concern.

203
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,520
-Let me help.
-Thank you.

204
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:14,960
Thee.

205
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,120
Ms. Ruedi.

206
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,800
Mr. Tiwa is ready for lunch.

207
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,160
Let's go.

208
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,280
Can you hear that?

209
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,160
Yes, sir.

210
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,120
Can you hear that?

211
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:47,000
Yes, sir.

212
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,160
Can you hear that?

213
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:56,600
Can you hear it?

214
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,040
Can you hear it?

215
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,240
Can you?

216
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:17,319
Your hearing is better than it was
last time you were here.

217
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,200
It is better, isn't it?

218
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:20,400
Yes.

219
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:23,800
He will be better soon.

220
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:34,440
Say yes if you can hear me.

221
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,120
Say anything else if you can't.

222
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:40,960
If I can't hear you,
why can't I just say no?

223
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:44,400
If I ask if you can hear me
and you reply, "No, I can't,"

224
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,000
I'll think you actually can hear me.

225
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,440
I see.

226
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,400
I can just say anything, then?

227
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,360
-Can you hear me?
-Yes.

228
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,720
Can you hear me?

229
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:04,920
-Dech.
-I'm asking if you can hear me.

230
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,240
Dech.

231
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,800
Why are you calling my name?

232
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:10,960
Can you hear me?

233
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:15,760
You told me to say anything else
if I couldn't hear you.

234
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:17,160
So I am.

235
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:18,440
Dech!

236
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:26,960
So this is the limit of
your hearing range.

237
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,600
Am I right?

238
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,520
Dech.

239
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,600
You can't hear me from here, either?

240
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,720
Can you hear me?

241
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:41,120
Why are you so kind to me?

242
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,680
Thanks, my friend.

243
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,320
Mek!

244
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,400
What do you think of me?

245
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:01,160
Could we still be friends

246
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,480
if I were to tell you…

247
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:07,040
I fancy you?

248
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,000
Dech.

249
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,520
What were you saying?

250
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:18,720
Say it again.

251
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,200
It was nothing.

252
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,200
I know what you said.

253
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:34,240
You do?

254
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:47,640
Dech.

255
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:50,160
How do you say "lotus"?

256
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:51,960
"Lotus."

257
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:54,800
Lo… Lo…

258
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:56,160
Lo… lotus?

259
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,720
What about "bridge"?

260
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:01,920
<i>Pont.</i>

261
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:03,920
<i>-Pont.</i>
<i>-Pont.</i>

262
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,120
<i>Pont.</i>

263
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,520
What about this?

264
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:08,440
MOM LUANG DECHAPATRAPEE
FRENCH

265
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:13,040
<i>Carnet de notes.</i>

266
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:14,200
What?

267
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,400
<i>Carnet de notes.</i>

