00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,840
<i>Carnet de notes.</i>

275
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:31,120
<i>Carnet de notes.</i>

276
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:45,720
MONSIEUR MEK WILL BE A MODEL STUDENT
TO YOUNG MASTER DECH.

277
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:05,120
Happy birthday!

278
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,200
I…

279
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:21,480
I wrote you a poem.

280
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:31,360
<i>May this year be full of happiness</i>

281
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:36,080
<i>Like a fearless flower garden</i>

282
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:42,200
<i>Together, you shall be with your beloved</i>

283
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:45,040
<i>And your love, a song so ardent</i>

284
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:49,720
<i>Happy birthday, my beautiful buddy</i>

285
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:53,960
<i>Let your joy overflow like a fountain</i>

286
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:59,360
<i>May you always find happiness</i>
<i>In the virtues you possess</i>

287
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:04,320
<i>And may your love go on without end</i>

288
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,480
Well done, Mr. Tiwa.

289
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,600
Did you write it all by yourself?

290
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:19,880
Father.

291
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:30,760
Well done, my son.

292
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:45,080
You have such elegant handwriting.

293
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:52,080
Well done, my son.

294
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:08,000
You raised him really well.

295
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:13,800
Thank you, Your Highness.

296
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:55,800
Did you sneak off to cry alone?

297
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:03,640
I simply wanted Ms. Ruedi and Tiwa
to savor this time with my father.

298
00:24:04,640 --> 00:24:06,640
It is all right to cry.

299
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:07,960
I cry too.

300
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:12,680
Thank you for what you did for Tiwa.

301
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:17,080
There are no parents
who don't love their children,

302
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:19,280
especially an adorable child like Tiwa.

303
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,320
I have something for you.

304
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:26,120
What is it?

305
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:29,400
Our photograph.

306
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,760
I chose two.

307
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:35,360
I'd like to keep one,
and for you to keep one.

308
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:37,840
Which one would you like?

309
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:42,560
I…

310
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:45,160
I'll go with this one.

311
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:47,160
As for this one where I'm smiling widely,

312
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,280
I'll let you keep it.

313
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:55,720
I have something for you too.

314
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:02,120
Not that.

315
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:08,360
Here.

316
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:10,960
I had it made specifically

317
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:12,800
so my photo fits in it.

318
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:14,720
You can carry it
on your person at all times

319
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:18,440
and feel like I am always there with you.

320
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:23,080
Thank you.

321
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:36,920
But honestly…

322
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,320
I'd rather have the real you with me.

323
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:47,360
Smile. It's your birthday.

324
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:55,640
Are you seriously not going to
give me the ring?

325
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:12,360
The flowers are beautiful, Your Highness.

326
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:17,280
Anything I tend is certain to flourish.

327
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:28,480
Pikul.

328
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:30,080
Come over here.

329
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:37,840
Yes, Your Highness?

330
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:41,520
Where are you taking all these things?

331
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:43,240
To the little house, ma'am.

332
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:45,800
What's going on at the little house?

333
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:48,600
POETRY

334
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:52,000
You even wrote on the back cover?

335
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:54,520
I'd used up the pages, but was afraid
I'd forget if I didn't write it down.

336
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:57,600
I'll get you more notebooks.

337
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:58,720
Would a dozen suffice?

338
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,240
It would, Father.

339
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:08,200
Try this.

340
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:11,040
Eat your fill, love.

341
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:16,720
Ram.

342
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:18,360
Thee.

343
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:22,800
Mother.

344
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:25,880
Who said you could have a party
for an outsider inside my house?

345
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:29,360
I invited Rati.

346
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:31,920
Go back to the palace.

347
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:35,600
Mother.

348
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,640
Father.

349
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,040
Mother, please.

350
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:07,640
I told you that I would only let that
Ruedi girl and her son stay here

351
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,440
if you never set foot in there.

352
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:11,800
I was simply--

353
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:15,520
Tell them to move out of
my house tomorrow.

354
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:19,240
Mother.

355
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:25,720
How long have you known
about your son and Rati?

356
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:29,640
What about Thee and Professor Rati?

357
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:33,200
So all you care about is yourself.

358
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,440
Don't you see how close they are?

359
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:40,520
If this is about me, please ask me
directly. I promise to be honest.

360
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:41,920
How arrogant.

361
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:45,360
I refuse to acknowledge
the shameful things you have done.

362
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:48,640
I'm afraid you can't avoid it forever,
seeing as Rati and I--

363
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:49,720
Ram.

364
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:53,080
I want your son to marry Lady Pa
as soon as possible.

365
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:54,640
Tomorrow even, if we can.

366
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:56,840
-Grandmother!
-Can you make it happen?

367
00:28:56,920 --> 00:29:00,800
If you can't, tell your mistress
to move out of my house today.

368
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:05,400
Yes.

369
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,800
Do whatever you want, Grandmother.

370
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,680
But please know…

371
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:22,800
I am no flower.

372
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:36,720
A hundred sacks of tea leaves, sir.

373
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:38,120
A hundred sacks of tea leaves?

374
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:39,440
CUSTOMS

375
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:48,960
Where is Baronet Dech?

376
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:52,040
I don't know, sir.

377
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:54,360
He did not come to work today.

378
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,440
If he's gone during working hours,

379
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:02,800
where is he?

380
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:10,200
Sir, please!

381
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:14,520
My son didn't go to work.

382
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:16,640
Do any of you know something
that you've kept from me?

383
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:18,760
-We don't know anything, my lord!
-We really don't, sir.

384
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:51,520
MONSIEUR MEK WILL BE A MODEL STUDENT
TO YOUNG MASTER DECH.

385
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:02,120
To Talad Noi, please.

386
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:03,880
Of course. Please.

387
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:07,640
Good to go?

388
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:11,120
Hold on.

389
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:13,000
Come on, girls.

390
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:18,400
You don't mind, do you?

391
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:22,360
-Let me help.
-Dech?

392
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,840
All right.

393
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:26,000
Shall we?

394
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:27,120
Of course.

395
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:28,320
Ready?

396
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:32,520
One, two… three!

397
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:33,880
Let's go, Dech.

398
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:46,400
Here.

399
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:48,680
-Thank you.
-Oh?

400
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:49,600
You…

401
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:51,440
You look just like the son
of that nobleman.

402
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:53,280
What's his name, again?

403
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:57,160
Hey, what nobleman pulls
a rickshaw, ladies?

404
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,840
I think you got the wrong man.

405
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,680
Maybe it's not him. Let's go.

406
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:03,280
You girls lose control
whenever you see a handsome gentleman.

407
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,480
Let's just go.

408
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:17,400
Come on.

409
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:19,840
No one needs a rickshaw right now.
Come and study with me.

410
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,640
Don't you have to go to work?

411
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,640
I took the day off.

412
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:26,040
Dech.

413
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,600
You've taken too many days off.

414
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,400
Go to work.

415
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:31,520
We can study later.

416
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:34,000
And you don't have to help me
with my work anymore.

417
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,760
Are you accusing me of interfering?

418
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:41,520
If you get recognized again,
what will you say?

419
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,200
I don't want you to be
in trouble with your father.

420
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:47,360
So you really want me to go?

421
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:50,920
To Phraya Krai Temple.

422
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:57,680
I want to be a news translator too.

423
00:32:57,760 --> 00:33:00,280
I don't often want
to do something for myself.

424
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:01,880
You can't stop me.

425
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:04,840
Dech.

426
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:06,920
You're as stubborn as a mule.

427
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,920
-Dech.
-Mek.

428
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:12,320
Are you going to keep talking?
I'm in a hurry!

429
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:14,680
Please, sir.

430
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:18,880
I'll help.

431
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:22,040
Where to, sir?

432
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:23,240
Phraya Krai Temple.

433
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:24,760
Of course.

434
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:28,000
Good to go, sir?

435
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:40,520
Hey, anyone not busy?

436
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:42,560
Come help me get these things on the cart.

437
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,400
I got it.

438
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,000
Oh, Mek. Good.

439
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:47,800
I'll help.

440
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:49,960
You were born a nobleman,

441
00:33:50,040 --> 00:33:51,480
but want to be a working commoner?

442
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:52,600
Father.

443
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:56,600
What have you done to my son?

444
00:33:58,680 --> 00:33:59,920
He has nothing to do with this.

445
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:03,080
The Young Master didn't do anything.
It was all my fault, sir.

446
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:07,000
He was injured and lost his hearing.
I'm only taking care of him.

447
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:11,800
What are you to him?
Why must you "take care" of him?

448
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:16,480
-What have you done to my son?
-Father!

449
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:17,880
Leave it!

450
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,080
Come here!

451
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:20,920
You two, beat him!

452
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,320
Stop it!

453
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:28,560
Mek!

454
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:33,520
Mek.

455
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:36,000
You lowlife! Stay away from my son!

456
00:34:38,320 --> 00:34:40,760
-Mek!
-Don't get in his way, Dech!

457
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:41,920
Father, stop!

458
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,440
Father, stop!

459
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:44,520
-Dech, no.
-Father!

460
00:34:46,239 --> 00:34:47,679
Father, please stop.

461
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:48,679
Dech.

462
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:07,040
THEE

463
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:16,720
Rati.

464
00:35:17,720 --> 00:35:18,680
Thee.

465
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:20,760
What did Her Highness say?

466
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:24,360
It's barely past your birthday.
Don't spend it worrying about nonsense.

467
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:27,120
Please tell me.

468
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:29,400
So we can work things out together.

469
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:32,480
Grandmother is, as expected, disgruntled.

470
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:36,320
She has ordered my father to set
the earliest date possible for my wedding.

471
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:42,520
I'm not going to marry someone
I'm not in love with.

472
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:48,600
But if Her Highness doesn't approve,

473
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:52,280
even if it is someone you are in love
with, this will prove to be difficult.

474
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:59,920
And… a man, no less.

475
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:05,520
I don't see how we can make this work.

476
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:09,480
Don't waste your time worrying.

477
00:36:10,240 --> 00:36:12,760
I'll talk to Grandmother tomorrow.

478
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:15,520
I'm coming with you.

479
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:16,720
No.

480
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:18,800
I must.

481
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:22,920
If you are going to talk to her about us,
then we have to do it together.

482
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,360
We must show her our sincerity.

483
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:29,120
I have no choice but to yield
when you get serious like this.

484
00:36:30,360 --> 00:36:31,400
You're right.

485
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:37,600
We'll talk to her tomorrow
after class then.

486
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,400
I agree.

487
00:37:00,560 --> 00:37:01,520
Mek!

488
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:18,480
They fired me, sir.

489
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:23,160
I don't work here anymore.

490
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:31,840
Please go home, Young Master.

491
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:35,760
I am only resting.

492
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:38,000
I will go home soon.

493
00:37:40,560 --> 00:37:42,080
Speak to me like you always do.

494
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:47,000
Mek!

495
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:51,360
Are you in pain?

496
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,560
I'm sorry.

497
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:02,520
Your father's men are still around, sir.

498
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:05,400
I'll talk to him.

499
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:08,600
I'll make him understand.

500
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:15,520
I told you.

501
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:19,240
Once I accept you as my friend,

502
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,720
you are mine for the rest of our lives.

503
00:39:30,600 --> 00:39:32,240
You were born a nobleman,

504
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:34,080
but want to be a working commoner?

505
00:39:34,680 --> 00:39:37,000
You lowlife! Stay away from my son!

506
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:28,000
You're finally here.

507
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,600
CIVIL SERVANTS SCHOOL

508
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:41,000
Do you know why the palace wants
Siamese officials to learn French?

509
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:45,920
To be able to communicate,
which would benefit both nations.

510
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:47,080
Am I right, Your Highness?

511
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:49,960
"Both nations."

512
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:55,160
Then how come only the Siamese
are learning French?

513
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:02,560
I hope you don't mind
my speaking so bluntly.

514
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:05,560
I am just an old lady in a small country

515
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:08,680
who doesn't know much about
the outside world.

516
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:12,320
You see, I had been living peacefully
the way I was used to…

517
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:15,480
but then one day,

518
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:18,640
a so-called ally came along

519
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:24,440
only to bring us the kind of war
that did incalculable damage.

520
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:29,160
Once that ally got what they wanted,

521
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:34,800
they departed, without caring about
the harm they left behind,

522
00:41:35,680 --> 00:41:42,320
leaving those who remained
to struggle alone to survive.

523
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:48,440
I understand you come from a free world.

524
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:55,800
But freedom does not mean you can freely
cause anybody harm, am I right?

525
00:41:58,240 --> 00:42:00,520
I may be French by nationality,

526
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:05,840
but I know and feel in my heart
that I am Siamese.

527
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:07,840
That is good then.

528
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:10,160
If you're Siamese,

529
00:42:10,240 --> 00:42:12,920
you probably understand what I'm saying.

530
00:42:16,920 --> 00:42:21,280
I won't allow my grandson
and the Wisut family

531
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:24,200
to be ruined by you.

532
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:26,200
Never.

533
00:42:45,920 --> 00:42:48,440
Why didn't you tell me that
Grandmother visited you at school?

534
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,280
What did she say?

535
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:56,680
Her Highness spoke nothing but the truth.

536
00:42:57,280 --> 00:42:58,160
Rati.

537
00:42:58,680 --> 00:43:01,560
She doesn't want me to ruin your life.

538
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:04,200
But you are not ruining my life.

539
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:10,760
No one knows about us right now.

540
00:43:11,480 --> 00:43:12,840
But once they do,

541
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:16,080
your reputation will be ruined,
and so will your family's.

542
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:19,160
By which time,
I will be safely back in France.

543
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:23,960
Her Highness spoke nothing but the truth.

544
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:28,080
Even so, I am not afraid.

545
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:32,720
I don't see how we can be happy together.

546
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:36,560
I won't allow you to break off
contact with me

547
00:43:36,640 --> 00:43:38,280
simply because my grandmother forbids it.

548
00:43:38,360 --> 00:43:39,280
Do you understand?

549
00:43:42,520 --> 00:43:44,680
Who says I'm going to do that?

550
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:47,400
Well…

551
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:50,400
Grandmother…

552
00:43:52,280 --> 00:43:54,160
She told you
to leave me alone, didn't she?

553
00:43:57,080 --> 00:43:59,000
She certainly has a right to forbid,

554
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:03,080
but I have a right
to make my own decision.

555
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:04,960
I don't know why,

556
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:07,800
but I believe what you said.

557
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:11,440
I believe that this thing between us
is possible.

558
00:44:12,880 --> 00:44:14,200
Do you mean it?

559
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:25,720
Mother Buaphan told us
to take good care of each other.

560
00:44:27,360 --> 00:44:29,320
So not only do I refuse to submit,

561
00:44:30,040 --> 00:44:32,120
but I am asking you to be my betrothed.

562
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:16,200
And I ask you to be mine.

563
00:45:56,360 --> 00:45:59,360
<i>I have consulted with the minister</i>
<i>about the date of your wedding.</i>

564
00:45:59,440 --> 00:46:00,800
<i>We have agreed on</i>
<i>the beginning of next month.</i>

565
00:46:00,880 --> 00:46:03,560
Do not worry about
what hasn't yet happened.

566
00:46:03,640 --> 00:46:05,600
<i>The best we can do is</i>
<i>make the most of today.</i>

567
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,120
I know my father better than anyone.

568
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:08,680
-We must run.
-Run?

569
00:46:08,760 --> 00:46:09,880
You die today.

570
00:46:09,960 --> 00:46:11,040
NEXT EPISODE

571
00:46:12,680 --> 00:46:14,200
Let me dry your hair.

572
00:46:14,280 --> 00:46:15,560
<i>I can do it myself.</i>

573
00:46:15,640 --> 00:46:16,800
Grandmother.
